//! # Resonance Knot — Rust port of the Lean format contract
//!
//! Mirrors `Gnosis.ResonanceKnotFormat` (and the five sibling modules
//! `Encoder`, `Decoder`, `RoundTrip`, `CompressionBound`, `Correctness`)
//! from `open-source/gnosis-math/Gnosis/ResonanceKnot*.lean`.
//!
//! The Lean modules are the SSOT for the format and its theorems. This
//! Rust crate is a program that produces / consumes bytes matching that
//! format — its job is to encode an existing dense `.knot` (Llama-70B,
//! Gemma4-31B, etc.) as a spectral residual `.rknot`.
//!
//! ## Pass schedule (works backwards from "smaller file ships to R2")
//!
//! - **Phase 0** — `format`: data structures only.
//! - **Phase 1** — `writer` + stub `manifest`: encode any tensor against a
//!   naive `first-k indices` manifest. Measures the "shape regularity"
//!   bonus when the standing residual goes through fp48/bitwise packing.
//! - **Phase 2** — `calibration` + real `manifest`: hook the existing
//!   inference kernel's attention computation, capture per-dim Q/K/V
//!   amplitudes and phase alignment over a probe corpus, derive real
//!   per-layer manifests via `extract_value_gated`.
//! - **Phase 3** — wire into `cloudbuild-llama-70b-to-knot.yaml` as a
//!   parallel step that uploads `.rknot` alongside `.knot`.
//! - **Phase 4** — round-trip verify against the dense `.knot` on the
//!   "Paris" capital-of-France probe.

pub mod bitwise_fp48;
pub mod bitwise_pack;
pub mod calibration;
pub mod decoder;
// dense_reader requires `std::fs::File` + native I/O and only feeds the
// native `encode-rknot` / `verify-rknot` binaries. Gate it off the wasm32
// build (the wasm pipeline never reads `.knot` files from disk — it
// streams tensor bytes from the JS host through `WasmHostBackend`).
#[cfg(not(target_arch = "wasm32"))]
pub mod dense_reader;
pub mod encoder;
pub mod encoder_config;
pub mod format;
pub mod manifest;
pub mod manifest_from_pca;
pub mod manifest_real;
pub mod reader;
#[cfg(not(target_arch = "wasm32"))]
pub mod rknot_backend;
pub mod saturation_metadata;
#[cfg(not(target_arch = "wasm32"))]
pub mod sketch_backend;
pub mod writer;
